'''''Star Wars'' 27''' is the twenty-seventh issue in the ''[[Star Wars: Republic]]'' series of [[Star Wars comic books|comics]]. It was published on [[February 28]], [[2001]] by [[Dark Horse Comics]].

==Publisher's summary==
''This issue, meet Jedi Yoshi Raph-Elan. On his way to a meeting of Jedi, Yoshi is attacked by an unknown enemy. Stranded without even a lightsaber, he must find out what this new threat wants. Along the way, he meets the beautiful princess Lourdes, and learns a lesson about trusting ancient prophecies. And it's all brought to you by Doug Petrie (''Buffy: Ring of Fire'' and writer for the ''Buffy'' TVS TV series), Randy Green (''Witchblade''), and Andy Owens (''Buffy'' and ''Angel'').''

==Plot summary==
In transit, newly [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Knighted]] [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] Yoshi Raph-Elan finds himself attacked by unknown assailants. One of the ships hits him, disabling his craft, and forcing him to crash-land on a nearby planet. After finding his ship worthless, and his lightsaber smashed, Yoshi heads off for a nearby village. Upon his arrival, Yoshi finds a small child about to be shot by a battle-droid. After saving the child and dispatching the droid, he heads off in search of the droid's master. His search takes him to a large castle. In an attempt to infiltrate the castle, Yoshi is discovered by Princess [[Lourdes]], who is intended to marry the droids' master, Lord [[Gar-Oth]]. The princess brings Yoshi with her to a reception of Lord Gar-Oth, in hopes he can help against the conqueror. But when Gar-Oth declares his intentions to marry Lourdes right then and there, Yoshi lies, saying he is her husband. Gar-Oth [[Battle of unidentified planet (Yoshi Raph-Elan)|attacks]] him, but upon realizing he is a Jedi, he unveils his giant [[Goliath (droid)|Goliath droid]], which he orders to attack the Jedi. After the princess kills Gar-Oth, Yoshi is able to use the giant droid's own circuitry to repair his lightsaber, which he uses to destroy the droid. Later, a republic ship is sent to rescue the young Jedi, but not before Lourdes kisses Yoshi telling him to return to her.

==Continuity==
During the comic, the speech of a number of aliens was depicted as Greek letters jumbled together.

The events of this comic as they relate to Princess Lourdes are retold in ''[[The Official Star Wars Fact File 128]]'', along with some new background information.

''[[The Essential Atlas]]'', released in [[2009]] provided further detail on two species depicted in this comic, the [[Yahk-Tosh]], and a previously unnamed species now identified as the [[Jilruan/Legends|Jilruans]].<ref name="The Essential Atlas">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>

